social_posts.post_text:
To the Clippers family,

I want to thank you for embracing me and my family 3 years ago. You guys welcomed us with open arms when I was at the lowest point of my career and helped me be a part of this organization. 

I want to thank Mr Ballmer and the front office for the great opportunity and the trust they gave me. 

Thanks to Ty Lue and his staff who saved my career. Ty, thank you for believing and trusting me from DAY 1. I’ll be forever ever grateful for what you’ve done for me and my family. 

Thank you to my teammates, it’s been a great ride and I wish you all the best 🙏🏽.

To the fans, I tried to give you my best each and every night, every game (even in the 4th quarter…), even playing the day of the birth of my daughter and not missing a single game after that 😅.

Batum Battalion, the French knight will be forever thankful to you 🫡 

Now time to move on to my next chapter in Philly. Go 76ers!!!
Time flies, 1000 games in this league… The journey continues, to the next 1000 🙃

« J’étais un peu surpris quand même ! » 🗣️

Quand Nicolas Batum apprenait son trade aux Sixers.
